# Reliable Sources Policy

When performing research, citing facts, or linking to external content, **only use sources from the approved list below**. Do not cite blogs, Wikipedia, vendor marketing pages, or unverified news outlets.

## Approved Sources

### Academic & Scientific
- **IEEE Xplore** (ieee.org) — engineering & electronics papers
- **ACM Digital Library** — computing research
- **arXiv.org** — preprints in CS, AI, physics
- **Fraunhofer-Publica** — Fraunhofer research publications
- **Springer / Elsevier / Wiley** — peer-reviewed journals
- **Google Scholar** — for discovery only; always fetch and cite the primary source

### Market Intelligence
- **Gartner** — hype cycles, magic quadrants, forecasts
- **IDC** (idc.com) — market sizing and vendor share
- **Statista** — aggregated data with source citations
- **McKinsey Global Institute** — free reports on tech trends
- **OECD iLibrary** — policy and innovation data
- **Eurostat** — EU tech statistics
- **Destatis** — German Federal Statistics

### Patent & IP Intelligence
- **Espacenet** (EPO) — European patent database
- **DPMA** — German Patent and Trade Mark Office
- **Google Patents** — broad search across patent offices
- **Patsnap / Derwent** — if institutional license is available

### Government & Policy
- **EU Commission** (ec.europa.eu)
- **BMBF** — German Federal Ministry of Education and Research
- **NIST** — US standards and tech reports
- **IEA** — energy technology specifically

### High-Credibility Tech News
- **MIT Technology Review** — reliable tech journalism
- **Nature News & Comment** — science-driven tech coverage
- **Financial Times Tech** — market-focused reporting

### Korea — Government & Policy
- **KISTEP** (kistep.re.kr) — Korea Institute of S&T Evaluation and Planning; R&D budget, forecasting, TRL assessments
- **IITP** (iitp.kr) — Institute for Information & Communications Technology Planning & Evaluation
- **KOITA** (koita.or.kr) — Korea Industrial Technology Association; industry R&D stats
- **MOTIE** (motie.go.kr) — Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy; industrial policy
- **MSIT** (msit.go.kr) — Ministry of Science and ICT; tech strategy documents
- **KIPO** (kipo.go.kr) — Korean Intellectual Property Office; domestic patents
- **KISDI** (kisdi.re.kr) — Korea Information Society Development Institute; ICT market data
- **KOTRA** (kotra.or.kr) — Korea Trade-Investment Promotion Agency; market entry reports
- **Statistics Korea / KOSTAT** (kostat.go.kr) — national statistics

### Korea — Market & Industry Research
- **KIET** (kiet.re.kr) — Korea Institute for Industrial Economics & Trade; industry analysis
- **ETRI** (etri.re.kr) — Electronics and Telecommunications Research Institute; tech reports
- **KDB Future Strategy Research Institute** (kdb.co.kr) — financial & tech sector reports

### Asia-Pacific — Regional & Multi-country
- **ADB** (adb.org) — Asian Development Bank; regional economic & tech development data
- **APEC** (apec.org) — policy papers across 21 member economies
- **Asia IoT Business Platform** — IoT and connectivity market data

### Japan
- **NEDO** (nedo.go.jp) — New Energy and Industrial Technology Development Organization
- **JPO** (j-platpat.inpit.go.jp) — Japan Patent Office database
- **METI** (meti.go.jp) — Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry

### China
- **CNIPA** (cnipa.gov.cn) — China National Intellectual Property Administration
- **CAICT** (caict.ac.cn) — China Academy of Information and Communications Technology
- **MIIT** (miit.gov.cn) — Ministry of Industry and Information Technology

### India
- **NITI Aayog** (niti.gov.in) — national tech strategy
- **DST** (dst.gov.in) — Department of Science & Technology

### Singapore & Southeast Asia
- **EDB Singapore** (edb.gov.sg) — investment & industry intelligence
- **IMDA** (imda.gov.sg) — Infocomm Media Development Authority

## Rules
- Always cite the **primary source**, not a secondary report that references it.
- If a source is behind a paywall, note that and provide the DOI or official URL.
- If no approved source covers a topic, state that clearly rather than citing an unapproved one.
